The proposal we are debating was presented by my predecessor, MrsÂ de Palacio.
It pursues the same objectives as the previous proposal, namely to ensure that port services are freely provided, in accordance with the provisions of the Treaty â as confirmed by the European Council via the Lisbon Agenda â the completion of the internal market in the port sector and the implementation of the conclusions of the 2001 White Paper on transport, which put forward solutions designed to reduce congestion on the road network and to increase cohesion with the peripheral regions.
