We need a ports directive that can establish the framework for free competition between service providers in ports and also for such freer competition between ports as will provide a safeguard against state aid that distorts competition.
The Commissionâs very point of departure is that, by putting an end to the monopolies, we could obtain more efficient and better run ports.
We should then see more goods transported by ship, something that would reduce the burden on both the roads and the environment.
